node.text:
Please tell me y‚Äôall new @lettucefeastla was black owned!  Yup that‚Äôs right, one of the most infamous vegan food trucks in the game that I‚Äôm pretty sure you guys are already following, but if not, run that button all the way up and support whenever you can.  They are literally out in these streets feeding the community plant-based greatness.
‚Äî
Chef @skylertanksley here and I‚Äôve decided to spend this #blackouttuesday a little different.  Instead of posting a black screen that I feel actually drowns out and oppresses important information about the current injustices that are currently happening all around the world at this very moment.. I‚Äôve decided to share some pretty damn good vegan food created by phenomenal black-owned business‚Äô and chefs on the west coast.  This is done in hopes that our munch members who support us and what we do, go out and support these beautifully colored humans and what they do as well.

node.text: Giant Vegan Mozzarella Sticks made in-house from scratch daily... Need we say more? üòç

Oh don‚Äôt you worry I‚Äôm not here to share you the violent video you‚Äôve probably already seen.  I‚Äôm here to show you the non-violent video that was the start to a cold-blooded murder of #GeorgeFloyd.  If you don‚Äôt understand why us POC say we are scared to get pulled over, this video of a non-resist arrest is why.. Our entire time spent on American soil (that was stolen land from our indigenous brothers and sisters) us African Americans have been enslaved, mocked, patronized and murdered.  When all we have offered in return for these last two centuries have been strength, culture, community, passion, and most importantly of all HELP.  As an African American with a black father who was a police officer for +25 years AND NEVER FIRED HIS WEAPON ONCE WHILE ON THE LINE OF DUTY.  I‚Äôve come to understand that there are good cops and there are bad ones.  My Dad also agrees with me on this.. Just as there are good students in class and then there are ones who don‚Äôt represent the ethics or upholds the standards that school stands for.  Which means to me, just like in school, the bad police officers MUST HAVE CONSEQUENCES AND MUST BE SERVED JUSTICE.  Im blessed to be one of the African Americans still alive today and be just one of many to prove that our history of adversity, perseverance, and courage has pushed us to the point of top-tier success in many industries.  With this success comes a stronger voice, a voice we will use to strengthen the awareness of cruelty in its entirety, because as of right now to me, this seems to be one of the only effective tools to do so. - Chef @skylertanksley
#BLACKLIVESMATTER
